fields.name: code
fields.description: Inline code to execute (alternative to filePath)

fields.name: person
fields.description: AI agent to use for decision making

fields.name: judge_by
fields.description: Prompt for LLM to make a judgment

fields.description: Memory control strategy (e.g., GOLDFISH for fresh evaluation)

fields.name: at_most
fields.description: Maximum messages to keep in memory

fields.name: expose_index_as
fields.description: Variable name to expose the condition node's execution count (0-based index) to downstream nodes

fields.name: skippable
fields.description: When true, downstream nodes can execute even if this condition hasn't been evaluated yet

fields.name: file
fields.description: File path or array of file paths

fields.description: Serialize structured data to JSON string (for backward compatibility)

node_specs.description: Executes hooks at specific points in the diagram execution

fields.name: command
fields.description: Shell command to run (for shell hooks)

fields.name: resource_id
fields.description: Resource identifier (e.g., page ID, channel ID)

node_specs.description: Execute tasks using AI language models

fields.name: first_only_prompt
fields.description: Prompt used only on first execution

fields.name: first_prompt_file
fields.description: External prompt file for first iteration only

fields.name: memorize_to
fields.description: Criteria used to select helpful messages for this task. Empty = memorize all. Special: 'GOLDFISH' for goldfish mode. Comma-separated for multiple criteria.

fields.name: at_most
fields.description: Select at most N messages to keep (system messages may be preserved in addition).

fields.name: ignore_person
fields.description: Comma-separated list of person IDs whose messages should be excluded from memory selection.

fields.name: tools
fields.description: Tools available to the AI agent

fields.name: text_format
fields.description: JSON schema or response format for structured outputs

fields.name: text_format_file
fields.description: Path to Python file containing Pydantic models for structured outputs

fields.name: resolved_first_prompt
fields.description: Pre-resolved first prompt content from compile-time

fields.name: batch
fields.description: Enable batch mode for processing multiple items

fields.name: batch_input_key
fields.description: Key containing the array to iterate over in batch mode

fields.name: max_concurrent
fields.description: Maximum concurrent executions in batch mode

fields.name: trigger_mode
fields.description: How this start node is triggered

fields.name: custom_data
fields.description: Custom data to pass when manually triggered

fields.name: hook_filters
fields.description: Filters to apply to incoming events

node_specs.description: Execute another diagram as a node within the current diagram

fields.name: diagram_name
fields.description: Name of the diagram to execute (e.g., 'workflow/process')

fields.name: input_mapping
fields.description: Map node inputs to sub-diagram variables

fields.name: output_mapping
fields.description: Map sub-diagram outputs to node outputs

fields.name: wait_for_completion
fields.description: Whether to wait for sub-diagram completion

fields.name: isolate_conversation
fields.description: Create isolated conversation context for sub-diagram

fields.name: ignoreIfSub
fields.description: Skip execution if this diagram is being run as a sub-diagram

fields.name: diagram_format
fields.description: Format of the diagram file (yaml, json, or light)

fields.name: batch
fields.description: Execute sub-diagram in batch mode for multiple inputs

fields.name: batch_input_key
fields.description: Key in inputs containing the array of items for batch processing

fields.name: preprocessor
fields.description: Preprocessor function to apply before templating

node_specs.description: Parses TypeScript source code and extracts AST, interfaces, types, and enums

fields.name: extractPatterns
fields.description: Patterns to extract from the AST

fields.name: includeJSDoc
fields.description: Include JSDoc comments in the extracted data

fields.name: transformEnums
fields.description: Transform enum definitions to a simpler format

fields.name: flattenOutput
fields.description: Flatten the output structure for easier consumption

fields.name: outputFormat
fields.description: Output format for the parsed data

fields.name: batchInputKey
fields.description: Key to extract batch items from input
